The paper proposes a novel dynamic planning strategy for performing a sequence of navigation and manipulation steps involving objects in unstructured human environments. This involves training a score function based on Markov Random Field (MRF) using a maximum margin learning method. The paper also discusses the generalization of the approach to unseen scenarios. Based on these aspects, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. The paper involves working with objects in an environment, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves planning and control of a system, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
